t">Geometry of space-time to be considered.</span></p></td><td style="border-bottom-color:#000000; border-bottom-style:solid; border-bottom-width:0.5pt; border-left-color:#000000; border-left-style:solid; border-left-width:0.5pt; border-right-color:#000000; border-right-style:solid; border-right-width:0.5pt; border-top-color:#000000; border-top-style:solid; border-top-width:0.5pt; padding-left:5.4pt; padding-right:5.4pt; vertical-align:top; width:70.8pt"><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">- Network Rail, RSSB, ORR</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p></td></tr><!--[if !supportMisalignedColumns]><tr style="height:0pt"><td style="width:19.6pt; border:none"></td><td style="width:35.45pt; border:none"></td><td style="width:14.15pt; border:none"></td><td style="width:63.8pt; border:none"></td><td style="width:42.55pt; border:none"></td><td style="width:49.6pt; border:none"></td><td style="width:56.7pt; border:none"></td><td style="width:56.7pt; border:none"></td><td style="width:64.35pt; border:none"></td><td style="width:70.8pt; border:none"></td></tr><![endif]--></table><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">The Table 1 shows that human (latent failures) committed by various stakeholder(s) organisations dominate the rare and bad event of a cyclist</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">’s</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> accidental death.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">From the partial HAZOP </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">study it can be inferred that accelerating train relative to the cyclist is an occupational hazard. Because in a relative (from Albert Einstein’s perspective) universe, inertial path is greater than accelerated path or in geometric terms, the diagonal of a</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> triangle is more than sum of it sides is shown by Sir Roger Penrose</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">(Penrose, 2004)</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">. These findings are counter –intuitive to </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">ancient Greek (Pythagoras theorem) and 17</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:7.33pt; vertical-align:super">th</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> Century (Newtonian dynamics) physics</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">(Reason, 1990)</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">.  </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">The HAZOP Study can be applied to all other interfaces requiring a study. Similar detailed studies were performed by author and published</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">(Appicharla, 2006)</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">(Appicharla, 2010)</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">, </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">(Appicharla, 2012)</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">(Appicharla, 2013)</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Having established </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">the fact that the Train Regulating and Controlling </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">System can induce errors and contribute a collision hazard,</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> it is necessary to pay attention to the barriers that can prevent and protect the cyclist from this occupation hazard</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="color:#4f81bd; font-family:Calibri; font-size:9pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="color:#4f81bd; font-family:Calibri; font-size:9pt; font-weight:bold">Table </span><span style="color:#4f81bd; font-family:Calibri; font-size:9pt; font-weight:bold">2</span><span style="color:#4f81bd; font-family:Calibri; font-size:9pt; font-weight:bold">: Energy Barrier Trace </span><span style="color:#4f81bd; font-family:Calibri; font-size:9pt; font-weight:bold">Analysis </span><span style="color:#4f81bd; font-family:Calibri; font-size:9pt; font-weight:bold">Model </span><span style="color:#4f81bd; font-family:Calibri; font-size:9pt; font-weight:bold">(EBTA) </span></p><table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" style="border-collapse:collapse; margin-left:16.2pt; width:465.75pt"><thead><tr><th style="border-bottom-color:#000000; border-bottom-style:solid; border-bottom-width:0.5pt; border-left-color:#000000; border-left-style:solid; border-left-width:0.5pt; border-right-color:#000000; border-right-style:solid; border-right-width:0.5pt; border-top-color:#000000; border-top-style:solid; border-top-width:0.5pt; padding-left:5.4pt; padding-right:5.4pt; vertical-align:top; width:61.8pt"><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Hazard ( Energy trigger) </span></p></th><th style="border-bottom-color:#000000; border-bottom-style:solid; border-bottom-width:0.5pt; border-left-color:#000000; border-